## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one agent matches. |

This data source resolves **both** user agents (`chat`, `background`) and
builtin agents (`builtin_*`), which are otherwise read-only and not manageable
through the resource.

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Agent integer ID. |
| `name` | Agent name. |
| `type` | One of `chat`, `background`, `builtin_chat`, `builtin_background`, `builtin_quick_action`, `builtin_session_assist`. |
| `description` | Agent description. |
| `model_id` | ID of the pinned `mistershell_ai_model`, or null if the agent uses the default model. |
| `system_prompt_id` | ID of the `mistershell_ai_prompt` the agent renders. |
| `config` | Agent execution config JSON (token_budget, max_steps, max_tokens, temperature, top_p, max_execution_time_seconds, and builtin-only keys capability/label/icon). Not sensitive. |
| `is_builtin` | `true` for `builtin_*` agents (managed by MisterShell). |
| `is_functional` | Whether the agent has a usable model. |
| `tool_ids` | Set of restricted tool IDs; empty = all tools allowed. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

For the full `type` enum, the builtin agent list, the complete `config` field
set, and the `tool_ids` semantics, see the
[`mistershell_ai_agent` resource](../resources/ai_agent.md) page.
